Sri Lanka beat hosts Bangladesh by 79 runs in the tri-nation series final in Dhaka a short while ago.Batting first, Sri Lanka made 221 before being bowled out.In reply, Bangladesh batsmen were all out for 142 in 42.1 overs.Debutant Shehan Madushanka made it a memorable game by bagging a hattrick. He captured the last 3 wickets.Mahmudullah was the top scorer for the home side with 79.